1
00:00:05,761 --> 00:00:07,521
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,521 --> 00:00:09,131
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,031 --> 00:00:12,331
Gi Cheol.

4
00:00:13,631 --> 00:00:14,661
Gi Cheol...

5
00:00:14,661 --> 00:00:16,231
Hey, Jeong Han. Seong Mi.

6
00:00:16,831 --> 00:00:20,141
- Seong Mi. Jeong Han.
- What is it?

7
00:00:21,871 --> 00:00:24,311
- Jeong Han. Seong Mi.
- Mother.

8
00:00:24,371 --> 00:00:27,311
- Mom. What is it?
- He's gone.

9
00:00:27,441 --> 00:00:29,011
Your father is gone.

10
00:00:29,351 --> 00:00:32,351
- What?
- Father's gone?

11
00:00:32,551 --> 00:00:33,751
What do we do?

12
00:00:34,681 --> 00:00:36,821
But Father was sleeping.

13
00:00:37,591 --> 00:00:38,891
- Honey...
- What do we do?

14
00:00:39,821 --> 00:00:40,821
Father!

15
00:00:41,461 --> 00:00:42,461
Father!

16
00:00:43,031 --> 00:00:44,161
Father!

17
00:00:45,831 --> 00:00:48,771
What do I do? Father!

18
00:00:50,531 --> 00:00:51,671
Father!

19
00:00:54,841 --> 00:00:57,871
(Original Old-Fashioned Snack Shop)

20
00:00:58,571 --> 00:00:59,741
Gi Cheol.

21
00:01:01,511 --> 00:01:02,711
Yes, bye.

22
00:01:05,651 --> 00:01:06,751
Gi Cheol.

23
00:01:22,401 --> 00:01:23,571
That's Mi Hyang's car.

24
00:01:26,141 --> 00:01:28,701
Mi Hyang, stop.
You can't get caught.

25
00:01:29,011 --> 00:01:30,941
Run. It's the police!

26
00:01:30,941 --> 00:01:32,841
Run!

27
00:01:36,151 --> 00:01:37,981
Grandfather, where are you going?

28
00:01:38,511 --> 00:01:41,021
Let go. I have to go to Mi Hyang.

29
00:01:41,881 --> 00:01:43,591
Grandfather,
where are you trying to go?

30
00:01:43,851 --> 00:01:44,851
Mi Hyang...

31
00:01:45,491 --> 00:01:47,221
She didn't do anything wrong.

32
00:01:49,261 --> 00:01:52,061
Grandfather, can you please
look me in the eye?

33
00:01:52,661 --> 00:01:55,201
Grandfather, it's me, Woo Jae.
Your grandson.

34
00:01:58,131 --> 00:02:00,201
- My grandson?
- Yes.

35
00:02:00,971 --> 00:02:04,541
Grandfather, please follow me.
Take a deep breath in...

36
00:02:05,541 --> 00:02:06,711
and breathe out.

37
00:02:07,711 --> 00:02:10,181
Yes, good. One more time.
Take a deep breath in...

38
00:02:10,951 --> 00:02:12,151
and breathe out.

39
00:02:13,121 --> 00:02:16,691
Okay. Grandfather, it's okay.
I'll stay by your side.

40
00:02:21,461 --> 00:02:22,461
Father!

41
00:02:25,461 --> 00:02:28,061
How could you disappear like that
without a word?

42
00:02:29,271 --> 00:02:32,571
Dad, I think Grandfather
is having an anxiety attack.

43
00:02:33,971 --> 00:02:36,041
I was worried
you'd gotten into an accident.

44
00:02:36,571 --> 00:02:39,211
I was so worried, Father.

45
00:02:40,781 --> 00:02:41,841
I'm sorry.

46
00:02:45,111 --> 00:02:46,351
It's okay, Father.

47
00:02:47,151 --> 00:02:48,651
He's not hurt, is he?

48
00:02:48,721 --> 00:02:49,951
No, he's okay.

49
00:02:50,951 --> 00:02:52,051
Father.

50
00:02:52,761 --> 00:02:55,491
Let's go home, okay?
Let's go home, Father.

51
00:02:55,991 --> 00:02:56,991
Father.

52
00:03:02,061 --> 00:03:03,231
Yes, Woo Jae.

53
00:03:04,801 --> 00:03:05,901
Did you find him?

54
00:03:08,341 --> 00:03:11,011
Okay. I'll head home too.

55
00:03:11,511 --> 00:03:12,541
Okay.

56
00:03:42,771 --> 00:03:44,741
Is it something like
Stockholm syndrome?

57
00:03:45,341 --> 00:03:46,341
Yes.

58
00:03:46,581 --> 00:03:47,681
No, I mean...

59
00:03:48,111 --> 00:03:51,081
the fact that
he went looking for the woman...

60
00:03:51,081 --> 00:03:52,681
who locked him up and beat him.

61
00:03:53,321 --> 00:03:56,051
I think he still truly believes
she's his sister.

62
00:03:56,491 --> 00:03:58,451
Because for 30 years,
Grandfather lived...

63
00:03:58,521 --> 00:04:00,121
believing in and relying on her.

64
00:04:01,321 --> 00:04:03,761
I thought things would be fine
once he got his memory back.

65
00:04:04,731 --> 00:04:08,971
To correct his distorted thinking
and restore his daily life...

66
00:04:09,171 --> 00:04:10,971
it's going to take time, Mom.

67
00:04:15,641 --> 00:04:17,071
It's Dong Suk.

68
00:04:17,471 --> 00:04:18,471
Oh, really?

69
00:04:19,241 --> 00:04:20,641
Yes, Dong Suk.

70
00:04:22,211 --> 00:04:25,481
Is everything okay?
How's Father doing?

71
00:04:32,661 --> 00:04:33,661
Is that right?

72
00:04:34,961 --> 00:04:37,061
- Yes.
- Dolphin.

73
00:04:37,791 --> 00:04:39,001
Yes, Mother.

74
00:04:40,161 --> 00:04:41,201
Is that Mom?

75
00:04:42,031 --> 00:04:46,541
- Oh, Mom. How's Father doing?
- He's fine.

76
00:04:46,571 --> 00:04:49,311
- Okay.
- Mother, get some rest.

77
00:04:49,311 --> 00:04:50,541
We'll check out tomorrow...

78
00:04:50,571 --> 00:04:52,171
and head home
before it gets too late.

79
00:04:52,941 --> 00:04:54,441
Good night, Mother.

80
00:04:54,941 --> 00:04:56,051
Good night.

81
00:04:59,521 --> 00:05:02,691
My Dolphin is so beautiful.
You really are.

82
00:05:03,291 --> 00:05:05,451
Hold on, I need to make a call too.

83
00:05:07,991 --> 00:05:09,031
(Ji Hu)

84
00:05:12,191 --> 00:05:13,261
Ji Hu.

85
00:05:14,331 --> 00:05:18,371
It's Dad. Yes.
Where else? At the hotel.

86
00:05:18,771 --> 00:05:21,571
Yes. Ji Hu,
what's your grandfather doing?

87
00:05:22,001 --> 00:05:23,011
Is he sleeping?

88
00:05:23,411 --> 00:05:25,841
Oh, okay. Can you put
him on the phone?

89
00:05:26,581 --> 00:05:27,581
Yes.

90
00:05:31,511 --> 00:05:36,151
Yes, Father. Yes, it's me. Yes.

91
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:38,121
Father, right now...

92
00:05:39,121 --> 00:05:41,591
I'm at a hotel with your daughter.

93
00:05:42,991 --> 00:05:45,091
You must be crazy.

94
00:05:46,061 --> 00:05:47,331
This guy's a lunatic.

95
00:05:48,561 --> 00:05:49,931
Man, I'm jealous.

96
00:05:50,671 --> 00:05:53,001
Honey, Ji Hu is right there.

97
00:05:53,541 --> 00:05:54,701
Go, Mom!

98
00:05:55,241 --> 00:05:56,911
Hey, Ji Hu. You little rascal.

99
00:05:58,041 --> 00:05:59,341
What a bunch of lunatics.

100
00:06:00,281 --> 00:06:01,281
Yes.

101
00:06:02,311 --> 00:06:03,811
I'm crazy.

102
00:06:04,551 --> 00:06:06,581
I'm crazy about Dong Suk.

103
00:06:07,021 --> 00:06:08,621
Hang up, Tamin.

104
00:06:08,621 --> 00:06:10,551
I'm wearing the lingerie
Se Ri bought me.

105
00:06:13,861 --> 00:06:15,721
Don't you worry
and get some sleep, Father.

106
00:06:16,161 --> 00:06:17,161
Okay.

107
00:06:25,801 --> 00:06:26,871
He's nuts.

108
00:06:27,501 --> 00:06:28,801
Hello? You punk.

109
00:06:29,411 --> 00:06:31,471
- Why hang up, you shameless brat?
- Hey.

110
00:06:36,111 --> 00:06:38,551
What is it, Mom?
Are you jealous of my aunt?

111
00:06:38,951 --> 00:06:40,681
Maybe we should go on
a second honeymoon...

112
00:06:41,151 --> 00:06:42,151
to Hawaii?

113
00:06:42,521 --> 00:06:45,351
- Oh, good idea.
- Oh, no.

114
00:06:45,621 --> 00:06:47,291
Now that your aunt
is married and gone,

115
00:06:47,691 --> 00:06:49,231
the house feels so empty.

116
00:06:50,961 --> 00:06:54,761
Has our sofa ever felt
so empty before?

117
00:07:02,841 --> 00:07:03,841
Yang Hyun Bin.

118
00:07:04,571 --> 00:07:07,241
No matter how busy you are, you need
to look after your mom. Got it?

119
00:07:07,381 --> 00:07:12,281
With Min Seo and Dong Suk both gone,
imagine how empty she must feel.

120
00:07:12,721 --> 00:07:15,681
So come by and have a meal
with her every once in a while.

121
00:07:16,051 --> 00:07:17,891
All right, I'm hanging up. Okay.

122
00:07:18,851 --> 00:07:20,391
Was that Hyun Bin?

123
00:07:20,621 --> 00:07:24,361
Yes, it seems he's busy
with some project or something.

124
00:07:26,701 --> 00:07:29,101
Okay. Good night, honey.

125
00:07:29,631 --> 00:07:31,571
Should I turn off the light?

126
00:07:34,271 --> 00:07:35,401
What's wrong?

127
00:07:38,411 --> 00:07:39,841
Come sleep in the bed.

128
00:07:40,381 --> 00:07:41,741
Really?

129
00:07:45,381 --> 00:07:46,881
Yes. Score.

130
00:07:49,051 --> 00:07:50,651
The kids are doing well.

131
00:07:53,561 --> 00:07:55,461
Dong Suk married well.

132
00:07:56,991 --> 00:07:59,931
And it seems Dong Ik and his wife
are getting along better.

133
00:08:01,001 --> 00:08:02,461
Gi Cheol came back home too.

134
00:08:04,901 --> 00:08:07,401
Everything's back
in its proper place now.

135
00:08:09,911 --> 00:08:11,411
So I, too,

136
00:08:13,281 --> 00:08:15,211
must return to my place.

137
00:08:29,191 --> 00:08:31,561
Just wait a little longer, In Ok.

138
00:08:36,871 --> 00:08:39,171
(Taehan)

139
00:08:48,941 --> 00:08:50,351
Why did you hit me, sister?

140
00:08:50,411 --> 00:08:53,151
Don't call me that. I don't have
a younger brother like you.

141
00:08:53,221 --> 00:08:54,521
Then you have
even less reason to hit me.

142
00:08:55,381 --> 00:08:57,151
I hope you get struck by lightning
and die...

143
00:08:57,221 --> 00:08:58,691
you good-for-nothing piece of trash.

144
00:09:00,721 --> 00:09:02,461
- Are you laughing?
- Sorry.

145
00:09:06,201 --> 00:09:07,831
Hey, why did you hit me?

146
00:09:08,761 --> 00:09:09,771
Are you laughing?

147
00:09:10,101 --> 00:09:11,101
Sorry.

148
00:09:12,131 --> 00:09:15,271
- Follow me.
- Hey, wait a second. Hey, let go.

149
00:09:18,241 --> 00:09:19,241
Gosh...

150
00:09:20,181 --> 00:09:21,411
Hey, please.

151
00:09:23,011 --> 00:09:26,521
Come on, use your words, okay?
You're making a scene at the office.

152
00:09:26,581 --> 00:09:28,751
How could I possibly look any worse?

153
00:09:32,321 --> 00:09:34,061
How late were you out drinking?

154
00:09:34,461 --> 00:09:35,591
None of your business.

155
00:09:37,131 --> 00:09:39,661
What are you so mad about now?

156
00:09:40,531 --> 00:09:41,961
Strategic Planning Division?

157
00:09:42,401 --> 00:09:44,301
Are you siding with Director Baek
now, too?

158
00:09:45,301 --> 00:09:48,441
Then what do you want me to do?

159
00:09:48,501 --> 00:09:50,441
I can't go anywhere else
because of my contract extension.

160
00:09:50,511 --> 00:09:52,841
Are you sure?
You don't have a plan B, do you?

161
00:09:52,911 --> 00:09:54,781
What plan B?

162
00:09:55,311 --> 00:09:57,681
Gong Ju Ah's brand launch
is the alternative?

163
00:09:57,751 --> 00:09:59,581
And that you put all
sorts of employees on it?

164
00:09:59,681 --> 00:10:00,881
What are you plotting?

165
00:10:01,621 --> 00:10:05,591
What plot? You think any plot
would even work right now?

166
00:10:05,651 --> 00:10:08,091
Then why do you need all that money?

167
00:10:08,221 --> 00:10:09,591
You're going to give it to me,
right?

168
00:10:09,661 --> 00:10:11,431
You said you would.
You asked how much I needed.

169
00:10:12,261 --> 00:10:15,731
You could at least brief me
on what it's for.

170
00:10:15,801 --> 00:10:17,101
What is there to brief?

171
00:10:17,801 --> 00:10:19,201
I have to make sure
the Fashion Division employees...

172
00:10:19,271 --> 00:10:20,271
can make a living.

173
00:10:20,341 --> 00:10:22,371
I'm trying to get them
some investments.

174
00:10:22,441 --> 00:10:25,441
They were all thrown out
onto the street overnight.

175
00:10:26,341 --> 00:10:27,941
- Is that all?
- That's all.

176
00:10:27,941 --> 00:10:30,411
I don't believe you.
Are you lying to me?

177
00:10:30,551 --> 00:10:32,311
I won't tell anyone. Just tell me.

178
00:10:32,851 --> 00:10:36,951
I'm telling you, that's it.
It's really out of pity.

179
00:10:40,061 --> 00:10:42,561
A pity project?

180
00:10:43,231 --> 00:10:44,861
Yes, it's to help...

181
00:10:44,861 --> 00:10:47,301
the former employees
get back on their feet.

182
00:10:48,501 --> 00:10:50,401
With Hye Su's own money?

183
00:10:50,501 --> 00:10:53,171
It's an investment, I guess.
There aren't many other options.

184
00:10:53,401 --> 00:10:55,871
We'll be lucky if the designers
can come up with anything.

185
00:10:55,971 --> 00:10:58,371
Is it really necessary
to go that far?

186
00:10:58,511 --> 00:11:00,041
Public opinion hasn't been great...

187
00:11:00,111 --> 00:11:01,981
since we dissolved
the Fashion Division.

188
00:11:02,281 --> 00:11:04,381
And if the former employees
hold a grudge...

189
00:11:04,451 --> 00:11:05,981
it'll hurt the company's image.

190
00:11:06,451 --> 00:11:08,981
Besides, we're not even using
company money...

191
00:11:09,051 --> 00:11:12,551
- so what's the problem?
- Right, right.

192
00:11:13,261 --> 00:11:15,421
Fine. Do as you see fit.

193
00:11:15,721 --> 00:11:17,891
Well, I'm busy,
so if you'll excuse me.

194
00:11:25,901 --> 00:11:29,511
Next time you see him,
tell him to greet me properly.

195
00:11:31,241 --> 00:11:32,241
Yes, sir.

196
00:11:32,511 --> 00:11:34,011
So, should I just keep tracking...

197
00:11:34,011 --> 00:11:36,581
Hye Su and Director Yang's movements?

198
00:11:37,711 --> 00:11:40,621
Seeing what Director Yang is up to,
I have a pretty good idea.

199
00:11:41,051 --> 00:11:42,921
Watch how things play out
for a bit...

200
00:11:43,321 --> 00:11:45,221
and start learning my job.

201
00:11:45,851 --> 00:11:49,791
I'm going to create
a new face for Taehan.

202
00:11:50,891 --> 00:11:53,661
- A new face?
- In the name of Taehan...

203
00:11:54,301 --> 00:11:57,571
a landmark that everyone
will look up to.

204
00:11:58,131 --> 00:12:01,941
A landmark? Do you mean
a new company building?

205
00:12:02,341 --> 00:12:03,341
Exactly.

206
00:12:04,011 --> 00:12:06,241
But not just
an ordinary new building.

207
00:12:06,581 --> 00:12:08,811
It's about completely
rebuilding Taehan.

208
00:12:09,651 --> 00:12:12,581
- I see.
- Now that the Chairman is gone...

209
00:12:13,251 --> 00:12:15,681
Taehan must also prepare
for a new era.

210
00:12:22,521 --> 00:12:27,031
- Are these all designs by CEO Gong?
- Yes, she did all this in one day.

211
00:12:27,101 --> 00:12:30,501
So, is this going
to be our main look?

212
00:12:30,571 --> 00:12:34,271
- Yes, we'll handle the sub-line.
- Okay.

213
00:12:38,441 --> 00:12:42,081
Hey, a CEO can't just be away
from her desk for this long.

214
00:12:43,351 --> 00:12:46,721
I went to the tax office
to register the business.

215
00:12:55,621 --> 00:12:56,761
What about the brand name?

216
00:12:57,361 --> 00:12:59,531
- Pelliv.
- I don't like it.

217
00:13:00,061 --> 00:13:02,001
The whole team agreed on it.

218
00:13:03,301 --> 00:13:05,301
Anyway, everyone, pick up the pace.
Okay?

219
00:13:05,371 --> 00:13:07,571
We need to see results
as quickly as possible.

220
00:13:07,671 --> 00:13:10,771
Director Yang,
we're not vending machines.

221
00:13:10,841 --> 00:13:12,271
He's putting on too much pressure.

222
00:13:13,111 --> 00:13:16,281
Anxiety, yes,
it's fuel for creativity.

223
00:13:16,351 --> 00:13:18,311
Are you going to come here
and get in our way every time?

224
00:13:18,381 --> 00:13:22,221
Get in your way?
I just secured our funding.

225
00:13:28,361 --> 00:13:30,591
So you came here to show off?

226
00:13:30,691 --> 00:13:33,731
I'm not showing off.
I'm here to share our progress.

227
00:13:35,131 --> 00:13:36,771
- Let's go.
- Where?

228
00:13:36,771 --> 00:13:39,101
- We're going to look at fabrics.
- Me?

229
00:13:39,171 --> 00:13:41,571
The designers have to work.
You're the one who told us to hurry.

230
00:13:41,671 --> 00:13:42,671
Come on.

231
00:13:45,811 --> 00:13:46,911
We'll be back.

232
00:13:50,211 --> 00:13:53,551
- They're more fired up than dating.
- Right?

233
00:13:53,581 --> 00:13:55,181
It's gotten even more intense.

234
00:13:58,251 --> 00:13:59,721
This one's good...

235
00:14:03,331 --> 00:14:05,691
What am I, your pack mule?

236
00:14:06,361 --> 00:14:10,231
You said it was urgent.
Does it kill you to lend a hand?

237
00:14:10,301 --> 00:14:13,971
Come on, help me carry this.
My arms are about to fall off.

238
00:14:14,441 --> 00:14:17,741
Fine, then just give me this one.

239
00:14:18,771 --> 00:14:21,941
When we were dating, you acted like
you'd give me the stars...

240
00:14:22,011 --> 00:14:23,011
being all sweet.

241
00:14:23,081 --> 00:14:24,951
Now that we've broken up,
you're showing your true colors.

242
00:14:25,011 --> 00:14:27,051
Look who's talking.

243
00:14:27,381 --> 00:14:30,621
You're the one who said not to bring
personal feelings into work.

244
00:14:30,691 --> 00:14:32,351
I meant we should work
like professionals...

245
00:14:32,421 --> 00:14:34,161
not that you should lose
all human decency.

246
00:14:34,221 --> 00:14:38,161
I'm a perfectly decent person, okay?
Let's stop provoking each other.

247
00:14:41,061 --> 00:14:42,801
Where are you going now?

248
00:14:42,861 --> 00:14:44,571
I'm hungry, so I'm going to
get something to eat. Why?

249
00:14:45,201 --> 00:14:47,971
Wow, was she always like this?

250
00:14:54,541 --> 00:14:55,541
There.

251
00:14:55,981 --> 00:14:58,011
This looks good.

252
00:15:00,881 --> 00:15:04,221
Hey, why are you dunking all of it?
It's going to get soggy.

253
00:15:04,391 --> 00:15:07,091
Didn't you once say you liked
it better when it's soaked?

254
00:15:07,161 --> 00:15:09,731
That was when we were dating,
so I just went along with it.

255
00:15:09,791 --> 00:15:13,331
Gosh, I'm actually a dipper,
not a soaker.

256
00:15:14,501 --> 00:15:16,671
Then why don't you
just order your own?

257
00:15:17,201 --> 00:15:18,731
Fine.

258
00:15:19,201 --> 00:15:21,841
Excuse me. Could we get another
assorted fried platter over here?

259
00:15:21,901 --> 00:15:24,511
- Yes.
- So petty.

260
00:15:24,711 --> 00:15:27,411
- "Petty?"
- Yes. Petty and a big baby.

261
00:15:27,481 --> 00:15:29,541
- Hey.
- "Hey?" I'm older than you.

262
00:15:29,581 --> 00:15:31,311
You don't get to talk like that
just because you look old.

263
00:15:31,381 --> 00:15:32,381
Look old...

264
00:15:33,281 --> 00:15:35,251
Here you go,
this one's on the house.

265
00:15:35,321 --> 00:15:37,891
It's our buy-one-get-one
for couples event today.

266
00:15:38,421 --> 00:15:39,761
Thank you.

267
00:15:40,291 --> 00:15:42,691
We'll pay for it.
We're not a couple.

268
00:15:42,761 --> 00:15:45,761
Oh, you looked so good together,
I just assumed.

269
00:15:45,831 --> 00:15:48,931
- No, we aren't.
- He's just a younger guy I know.

270
00:15:49,361 --> 00:15:50,501
Younger?

271
00:15:53,201 --> 00:15:56,241
He lived abroad and got a little
too much direct sunlight,

272
00:15:56,301 --> 00:15:58,741
- so he aged prematurely.
- Prematurely?

273
00:16:00,741 --> 00:16:01,981
Oh, my.

274
00:16:02,581 --> 00:16:06,881
- Unbelievable.
- You should've worn sunscreen.

275
00:16:06,881 --> 00:16:07,951
Seriously?

276
00:16:11,221 --> 00:16:12,751
Dunking it like this is so good.

277
00:16:14,461 --> 00:16:16,461
What do you think?
It's you, Grandfather, right?

278
00:16:16,791 --> 00:16:17,791
So it is.

279
00:16:18,461 --> 00:16:20,031
It does look like me.

280
00:16:21,161 --> 00:16:23,601
The kids had it without me knowing.

281
00:16:26,131 --> 00:16:28,901
Woo Jae,
keep a close eye on Grandfather.

282
00:16:29,271 --> 00:16:30,271
Okay.

283
00:16:31,871 --> 00:16:34,811
That's right. Hold on to me tight
so I don't go anywhere.

284
00:16:35,581 --> 00:16:38,211
Are you making a joke, Grandfather?

285
00:16:40,581 --> 00:16:41,721
Don't worry.

286
00:16:42,221 --> 00:16:43,591
I'm not going anywhere.

287
00:16:44,291 --> 00:16:45,291
Okay.

288
00:16:51,731 --> 00:16:53,501
- We're home.
- We're back.

289
00:16:53,561 --> 00:16:56,771
Oh, you're back.
That took longer than I expected.

290
00:16:57,201 --> 00:17:00,341
What did the hospital say?
Do you have to get chemotherapy?

291
00:17:00,901 --> 00:17:04,311
For now, we've decided to just try
radiation therapy.

292
00:17:04,571 --> 00:17:07,811
Really? Oh, but I hear
that's difficult too.

293
00:17:07,881 --> 00:17:10,911
Mother, we should be glad
it's not chemotherapy.

294
00:17:11,711 --> 00:17:14,821
I'll take good care of her.
Don't worry too much, Mom.

295
00:17:15,721 --> 00:17:16,721
And Father?

296
00:17:16,991 --> 00:17:20,521
Oh, he's in his room with Woo Jae,
looking at old photos.

297
00:17:21,061 --> 00:17:25,161
But he seems more lucid today.

298
00:17:25,631 --> 00:17:27,431
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

299
00:17:33,171 --> 00:17:35,771
- Father, do you like it?
- I do.

300
00:17:36,911 --> 00:17:38,071
See? I told you...

301
00:17:38,471 --> 00:17:40,411
that he'd wear
whatever you give him.

302
00:17:42,941 --> 00:17:46,081
Father, let's go out
and get you a haircut.

303
00:17:46,211 --> 00:17:49,021
- And we'll get a picture taken.
- Okay.

304
00:17:49,791 --> 00:17:52,521
Father, you seem to be
in good spirits today.

305
00:17:52,651 --> 00:17:54,691
I feel great.
My head feels so clear...

306
00:17:54,691 --> 00:17:56,091
after not taking my medicine
for a few days.

307
00:17:56,421 --> 00:18:01,101
Father, you don't know what kind
of medicine it was, do you?

308
00:18:01,331 --> 00:18:02,701
I don't know.

309
00:18:03,171 --> 00:18:06,101
She said I'd die if I didn't,
so I just took whatever she gave me.

310
00:18:07,941 --> 00:18:11,941
- Father, let's go. We'll be back.
- Bye.

311
00:18:15,781 --> 00:18:19,821
What in the world was she feeding
a perfectly lucid man like him?

312
00:18:20,581 --> 00:18:24,621
I think she used long-term use of
painkillers to keep him in a daze.

313
00:18:24,851 --> 00:18:27,591
She must have been afraid
of his memories coming back.

314
00:18:27,791 --> 00:18:31,731
But why would she do that?
What grudge could she have held?

315
00:18:32,661 --> 00:18:33,661
I...

316
00:18:34,701 --> 00:18:37,101
I'll ask Jo Mi Hyang myself...

317
00:18:38,901 --> 00:18:42,271
why she did such a thing to us.

318
00:18:44,041 --> 00:18:45,741
There's a warrant out for her...

319
00:18:45,811 --> 00:18:48,081
so she'll be caught soon, Mother.

320
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:50,811
It's so infuriating.

321
00:18:52,651 --> 00:18:53,781
Unbelievable.

322
00:19:01,021 --> 00:19:04,791
Could you give my father
a nice, stylish haircut, please?

323
00:19:04,861 --> 00:19:06,161
- Yes.
- Right.

324
00:19:07,731 --> 00:19:12,171
It looks like his hair has just been
getting chopped off at home.

325
00:19:12,871 --> 00:19:14,141
Well...

326
00:19:15,541 --> 00:19:20,441
- Oh my, there's a big scar here.
- What? Where?

327
00:19:28,351 --> 00:19:30,951
Father, are you okay?

328
00:19:31,691 --> 00:19:35,121
I think I just remembered something.

329
00:19:36,261 --> 00:19:38,161
It looks like he was
hit with something.

330
00:19:38,661 --> 00:19:40,031
It doesn't look like he fell.

331
00:19:40,761 --> 00:19:42,861
Something like this
would have bled a lot.

332
00:19:43,471 --> 00:19:44,771
Since it wasn't stitched,

333
00:19:44,771 --> 00:19:46,741
it looks like
he didn't even go to a hospital.

334
00:19:47,371 --> 00:19:48,571
Well...

335
00:19:54,881 --> 00:19:59,251
You two seem to be doing well.
I'm so glad to see you're improving.

336
00:20:00,321 --> 00:20:02,151
It's all thanks to you, Dr. Han.

337
00:20:03,081 --> 00:20:06,921
Alright, let's stop here for today.
You've both done well today.

338
00:20:07,491 --> 00:20:09,321
- Thank you for the session.
- Thank you.

339
00:20:09,961 --> 00:20:14,901
Also, I heard you sent something
via Dae Han.

340
00:20:15,061 --> 00:20:17,431
It was nothing, really.

341
00:20:17,971 --> 00:20:21,801
Still... Here, this is...

342
00:20:23,271 --> 00:20:24,741
a silver spoon set.

343
00:20:25,771 --> 00:20:27,111
Thank you so much.

344
00:20:27,311 --> 00:20:29,181
Also, I had a traditional
mattress set...

345
00:20:29,241 --> 00:20:31,181
delivered to your
father-in-law's room,

346
00:20:31,311 --> 00:20:32,811
it should be arriving
at your home soon.

347
00:20:34,121 --> 00:20:35,781
So, how is your father-in-law?

348
00:20:36,721 --> 00:20:38,551
He's recovering slowly.
It seems like...

349
00:20:38,621 --> 00:20:40,561
his memory is gradually
returning, too.

350
00:20:40,721 --> 00:20:42,591
Oh, that's a huge relief.

351
00:20:44,331 --> 00:20:46,761
By the way,

352
00:20:47,461 --> 00:20:49,361
you know that our Hyun Bin
and your daughter...

353
00:20:49,431 --> 00:20:50,931
are working together again, right?

354
00:20:53,701 --> 00:20:56,711
Yes, and I only permitted it
on the condition...

355
00:20:56,711 --> 00:20:58,441
that I wouldn't hear about it.

356
00:20:59,471 --> 00:21:03,311
I'm just worried. Your son comes
to our house to tutor, and...

357
00:21:03,411 --> 00:21:04,811
Now, now, dear.

358
00:21:05,811 --> 00:21:08,151
No, at this rate, we'll have
in-laws on top of in-laws...

359
00:21:08,451 --> 00:21:10,751
I'm scared we're going to
become triple in-laws.

360
00:21:10,821 --> 00:21:12,021
Don't you worry at all.

361
00:21:12,251 --> 00:21:15,361
That will happen over
my father's dead body.

362
00:21:16,361 --> 00:21:19,161
Instead of worrying about things
that haven't happened,

363
00:21:20,131 --> 00:21:21,931
focus on yourself.

364
00:21:22,601 --> 00:21:25,201
Look, it's just that
she's been through a lot.

365
00:21:25,671 --> 00:21:28,641
Her daughter went to the US,
and Dong Suk got married.

366
00:21:29,771 --> 00:21:31,811
You have Empty nest syndrome.

367
00:21:34,011 --> 00:21:35,941
Empty nest syndrome?

368
00:21:36,581 --> 00:21:39,181
Is there a good solution, then?

369
00:21:39,611 --> 00:21:41,381
I recommend shopping.

370
00:21:42,081 --> 00:21:44,351
- What?
- It's a prescription...

371
00:21:44,351 --> 00:21:47,921
I often give to those
who tend to neglect themselves.

372
00:21:48,861 --> 00:21:50,691
Even when you drink a cup of tea,

373
00:21:50,761 --> 00:21:53,331
drink it from a fancy cup
that's just for you.

374
00:21:53,631 --> 00:21:57,131
Start by taking small steps
to treat yourself.

375
00:22:06,041 --> 00:22:07,081
Yes, Mother.

376
00:22:07,881 --> 00:22:09,541
Have they arrived yet?

377
00:22:10,051 --> 00:22:12,651
Yes, I'm on my way. Yes.

378
00:22:13,751 --> 00:22:16,791
Looks like Dong Suk has arrived
at her in-laws'.

379
00:22:17,021 --> 00:22:20,821
- Yes, she has. I should get going.
- Okay.

380
00:22:24,431 --> 00:22:28,231
I want to go too.
I want to see her too.

381
00:22:28,561 --> 00:22:30,931
Let's go get some tea, okay?

382
00:22:31,701 --> 00:22:33,301
- Let's go.
- I'm not going.

383
00:22:36,471 --> 00:22:39,471
- Welcome.
- Welcome.

384
00:22:40,111 --> 00:22:42,481
- We're home.
- We're home.

385
00:22:42,841 --> 00:22:44,311
Welcome, Dong Suk.

386
00:22:45,251 --> 00:22:47,881
Congratulations, Dong Suk.
And congratulations, Dae Han.

387
00:22:48,621 --> 00:22:50,591
Thank you, Mother,
and you too, Seong Mi.

388
00:22:51,251 --> 00:22:52,321
Let me give you a hug.

389
00:22:52,591 --> 00:22:53,591
Oh my.

390
00:23:00,761 --> 00:23:02,501
Mom, Father.

391
00:23:03,401 --> 00:23:05,131
We're officially
husband and wife now.

392
00:23:05,401 --> 00:23:06,841
We'll be very happy together.

393
00:23:07,301 --> 00:23:10,171
I'll take good care of you,
Mother and Father.

394
00:23:10,511 --> 00:23:12,941
What do you mean "take care of us?"
We're a family living together.

395
00:23:13,681 --> 00:23:16,951
Dong Suk, thank you
for becoming part of our family.

396
00:23:17,951 --> 00:23:20,821
- Father, would you say something?
- Yes.

397
00:23:21,881 --> 00:23:23,451
Welcome, daughter-in-law.

398
00:23:24,991 --> 00:23:27,021
Father, you remember me, don't you?

399
00:23:27,261 --> 00:23:30,091
You adored me like your own daughter
when I was young.

400
00:23:30,661 --> 00:23:32,061
And now she's your daughter-in-law.

401
00:23:32,931 --> 00:23:35,461
I don't remember right now,

402
00:23:36,031 --> 00:23:37,831
but I'll try my best to remember.

403
00:23:38,671 --> 00:23:39,671
Okay.

404
00:23:40,471 --> 00:23:45,141
So, how was your wedding night?

405
00:23:45,541 --> 00:23:47,881
Oh, come on.

406
00:23:48,211 --> 00:23:49,741
Hey, look at this guy.

407
00:23:54,881 --> 00:23:57,721
Tamin, it's so cozy. I love it.

408
00:23:58,051 --> 00:24:01,491
- They already hung up our picture.
- You're right.

409
00:24:02,961 --> 00:24:06,531
- Dolphin, you must be tired.
- No, I'm fine.

410
00:24:06,901 --> 00:24:08,231
Come on, you can't be.

411
00:24:08,501 --> 00:24:11,371
- Why don't we rest on the bed?
- I'm telling you, I'm fine.

412
00:24:11,571 --> 00:24:13,301
No, don't say that. Come here.

413
00:24:14,401 --> 00:24:15,571
Oh, come on.

414
00:24:16,601 --> 00:24:19,771
Let's change into something
comfortable. I need to go out.

415
00:24:20,141 --> 00:24:22,041
- Go where?
- To the kitchen.

416
00:24:22,041 --> 00:24:23,951
I need to see
what ingredients they have.

417
00:24:24,111 --> 00:24:26,551
- Why, are you hungry?
- No...

418
00:24:26,921 --> 00:24:30,551
- I want to make breakfast tomorrow.
- Oh, come on.

419
00:24:31,521 --> 00:24:34,621
You don't have to do that.
Come here.

420
00:24:34,861 --> 00:24:39,431
Let go. Everyone's still up.
Be quiet. They'll hear us outside.

421
00:24:39,631 --> 00:24:41,431
Really?

422
00:24:42,901 --> 00:24:44,201
So what?

423
00:24:46,731 --> 00:24:50,041
This is nice, having tea
and taking a walk, isn't it?

424
00:24:51,241 --> 00:24:53,611
Oh, should we go shopping?
Seong Mi... I mean...

425
00:24:53,681 --> 00:24:55,981
Dr. Han Seong Mi did tell me to.

426
00:25:07,821 --> 00:25:09,491
Hey, Hyun Bin?

427
00:25:09,821 --> 00:25:12,531
No, that young lady
from our new in-laws.

428
00:25:12,791 --> 00:25:15,931
- Oh, hello.
- Hey, what are you two doing here?

429
00:25:16,031 --> 00:25:18,771
We were just passing by.

430
00:25:19,401 --> 00:25:23,071
- What about you?
- Oh, this is CEO Gong's office.

431
00:25:23,371 --> 00:25:24,411
Where? Here?

432
00:25:24,911 --> 00:25:28,741
Oh, I see. Can I take a look inside?

433
00:25:28,941 --> 00:25:30,681
- What?
- Honey?

434
00:25:31,051 --> 00:25:32,811
No, never mind.

435
00:25:33,881 --> 00:25:36,881
- We'll head inside then.
- Okay. Go on. Yes.

436
00:25:37,551 --> 00:25:38,551
Wait a minute...

437
00:25:41,561 --> 00:25:43,091
Wait, where were they coming from?

438
00:25:43,161 --> 00:25:45,191
And why are they going in together?
Seriously.

439
00:25:45,491 --> 00:25:47,261
Honey. Stay out of it, all right?

440
00:25:47,331 --> 00:25:50,161
- Let's just go. Come on.
- Let me go. Just a second.

441
00:25:50,231 --> 00:25:51,231
Let's go to the department store.

442
00:25:59,611 --> 00:26:00,811
All right, everyone,
you can head home.

443
00:26:05,451 --> 00:26:06,881
Already?

444
00:26:07,321 --> 00:26:09,781
This is no time to be thinking
about work-life balance.

445
00:26:09,851 --> 00:26:12,021
Are you just working here
to keep an eye on us?

446
00:26:12,951 --> 00:26:15,491
I'm organizing the data
for the platform onboarding.

447
00:26:15,861 --> 00:26:18,431
If we're meeting
the marketing manager,

448
00:26:18,531 --> 00:26:20,701
we need to get the main samples out
as soon as possible.

449
00:26:20,761 --> 00:26:23,701
Then you should have arranged
for a sample studio first.

450
00:26:23,771 --> 00:26:26,801
Actually, I already contacted
Manager Oh...

451
00:26:26,871 --> 00:26:29,001
who was in charge of the sample
studio at Taehan Fashion.

452
00:26:30,071 --> 00:26:33,141
- Is he going to do it?
- No. He refused.

453
00:26:33,441 --> 00:26:36,081
He seems to have been hit hard
by the Fashion Division sell-off.

454
00:26:36,381 --> 00:26:38,611
He's gone back to his hometown
to take a break.

455
00:26:38,981 --> 00:26:40,181
So what do we do now?

456
00:26:40,481 --> 00:26:42,821
But he and CEO Gong
worked so well together.

457
00:26:42,881 --> 00:26:45,351
That's why CEO Gong
has to go herself.

458
00:26:45,891 --> 00:26:47,721
You're coming with me tomorrow.
To Gangwon Province.

459
00:26:47,821 --> 00:26:50,331
Seriously?
Why are you telling me this now?

460
00:26:50,391 --> 00:26:52,491
You should've told me sooner
so I could pack.

461
00:26:52,561 --> 00:26:54,761
Why would you pack? It's a day trip.

462
00:26:56,831 --> 00:26:58,931
We'll split the driving.

463
00:27:00,131 --> 00:27:02,241
I thought you told me
to just focus on the designs.

464
00:27:02,301 --> 00:27:04,541
This is a strategic collaboration
out of necessity.

465
00:27:05,071 --> 00:27:07,711
Fine. Pick me up
at my place in the morning.

466
00:27:10,581 --> 00:27:12,181
Well, well...

467
00:27:16,521 --> 00:27:18,421
Let's just meet here.

468
00:27:22,591 --> 00:27:23,591
Unbelievable.

469
00:27:24,131 --> 00:27:25,791
He's doing this on purpose,
isn't he? Right?

470
00:27:26,091 --> 00:27:29,301
Well, guys do act like that
when they're not interested.

471
00:27:29,361 --> 00:27:30,601
Well, I'm not interested either.

472
00:27:33,271 --> 00:27:35,201
I'm heading out.
You all can go home now.

473
00:27:39,311 --> 00:27:41,941
So that means neither of them
will be in tomorrow, right?

474
00:27:43,111 --> 00:27:46,311
Guess we can relax a bit
at work tomorrow.

475
00:27:46,311 --> 00:27:48,151
- Yes!
- Oh, yes!

476
00:27:50,621 --> 00:27:53,551
(Royal Icheon Rice)

477
00:28:11,971 --> 00:28:14,141
Mother, you're up already?

478
00:28:14,211 --> 00:28:17,381
Oh, why are you up so early?
Go back to sleep.

479
00:28:17,451 --> 00:28:21,051
- You have work today.
- But you have work too. I'll do it.

480
00:28:21,121 --> 00:28:23,081
Oh, honey.
It's easier if I just do it.

481
00:28:23,151 --> 00:28:24,151
Go on back inside.

482
00:28:24,791 --> 00:28:25,821
Hurry, go on.

483
00:28:26,221 --> 00:28:27,761
But I want to help.

484
00:28:29,561 --> 00:28:31,731
The rice tastes
especially good today.

485
00:28:32,261 --> 00:28:35,101
Oh, really? We ran out,
so I bought a new brand of rice.

486
00:28:35,161 --> 00:28:36,161
It's good, isn't it?

487
00:28:37,201 --> 00:28:39,901
It's so glossy and chewy.
It's delicious.

488
00:28:40,471 --> 00:28:42,771
Wow, with so many of us,

489
00:28:42,771 --> 00:28:44,171
it's so lively and crowded,
isn't it?

490
00:28:45,071 --> 00:28:48,141
I know. If Ju Ah were here,
we'd be a huge family.

491
00:28:48,781 --> 00:28:50,811
The house feels so full.

492
00:28:52,311 --> 00:28:55,151
- Oh, we're out of kimchi.
- What?

493
00:29:00,121 --> 00:29:03,861
Father, I'm going to start
seeing patients again today.

494
00:29:04,031 --> 00:29:06,331
You should come
to the clinic with me.

495
00:29:06,791 --> 00:29:07,801
Should I?

496
00:29:08,631 --> 00:29:09,631
Honey,

497
00:29:09,931 --> 00:29:12,971
- should I get your doctor's coat?
- I even have a coat?

498
00:29:13,131 --> 00:29:16,071
Of course, Father.
You were a doctor too.

499
00:29:16,141 --> 00:29:18,241
And when was that?

500
00:29:18,511 --> 00:29:19,571
Actually,

501
00:29:19,771 --> 00:29:23,611
Mom kept it perfectly preserved
for 30 years.

502
00:29:24,711 --> 00:29:25,781
Thank you.

503
00:29:26,311 --> 00:29:29,881
I'm not sure if it'll still fit.
Clothes shrink over time.

504
00:29:29,951 --> 00:29:32,021
And you seem to have gotten
a bit smaller, too.

505
00:29:36,291 --> 00:29:39,891
Woo Jae. Are you tutoring Ji Hu
over at their house?

506
00:29:40,161 --> 00:29:41,531
Yes, that's right.

507
00:29:41,831 --> 00:29:45,271
Oh, if you're not comfortable with that,
I can have Ji Hu come here.

508
00:29:45,501 --> 00:29:48,071
Or Woo Jae could just do it
at our store.

509
00:29:48,171 --> 00:29:52,311
Oh, I was just curious.
Don't worry about it.

510
00:29:52,371 --> 00:29:53,841
Okay.

511
00:29:54,381 --> 00:29:57,681
Oh, but Ju Ah left
without eating anything.

512
00:29:57,751 --> 00:29:59,051
I should have packed her
something to eat...

513
00:29:59,611 --> 00:30:01,381
She's been so busy lately.

514
00:30:02,151 --> 00:30:05,221
That girl can take care of herself.
Don't you worry, Dong Suk.

515
00:30:05,351 --> 00:30:06,951
No, wait. It's sister-in-law, right?

516
00:30:08,561 --> 00:30:09,561
Okay.

517
00:30:10,631 --> 00:30:13,761
Oh, Woo Jae, have some of this.
I made it.

518
00:30:13,931 --> 00:30:15,201
Okay.

519
00:30:19,201 --> 00:30:20,201
This is delicious.

520
00:30:20,601 --> 00:30:22,301
Why did you sleep over?

521
00:30:22,701 --> 00:30:26,071
Well, the office for the business
with Jeong Han's daughter...

522
00:30:26,311 --> 00:30:27,841
is right here in Onjeong.

523
00:30:29,911 --> 00:30:33,581
You told me to stay for a meal
so Mother wouldn't feel lonely.

524
00:30:33,781 --> 00:30:35,621
Right, that was
the right thing to do.

525
00:30:36,381 --> 00:30:37,851
But, Hyun Bin.

526
00:30:38,391 --> 00:30:40,661
What are you doing
with Dr. Gong's daughter?

527
00:30:40,921 --> 00:30:43,261
I told you, it's business.

528
00:30:43,521 --> 00:30:48,331
- You have no personal feelings?
- Of course not.

529
00:30:49,261 --> 00:30:50,931
None at all.

530
00:30:51,531 --> 00:30:54,541
But Hyun Bin,
after the Chairman passed away,

531
00:30:54,601 --> 00:30:56,801
the Vice President
must be having a hard time, right?

532
00:30:57,311 --> 00:30:58,311
What?

533
00:30:58,871 --> 00:31:01,211
- Mom.
- Honey?

534
00:31:01,511 --> 00:31:05,051
What? I was just thinking
we could invite her over.

535
00:31:05,211 --> 00:31:07,321
Come on, it's not like we're strangers.
A home-cooked meal...

536
00:31:11,351 --> 00:31:12,351
I'm leaving.

537
00:31:12,791 --> 00:31:14,761
Hyun Bin. Hey, Hyun Bin.

538
00:31:14,821 --> 00:31:18,231
Good grief. That evil spirit
still hasn't been exorcised.

539
00:31:31,211 --> 00:31:33,671
Why are you here, Vice President?

540
00:31:35,481 --> 00:31:37,241
Because I'm the one
bankrolling this.

541
00:31:38,311 --> 00:31:41,781
I'm here to make sure
my money is being spent wisely.

542
00:31:42,621 --> 00:31:45,491
And here I thought
today would be an easy day.

543
00:31:46,821 --> 00:31:48,861
Stop slacking off
and get back to work.

544
00:31:49,221 --> 00:31:50,291
Move, move!

545
00:32:10,711 --> 00:32:12,981
Hey, let's try driving safely.

546
00:32:13,081 --> 00:32:16,781
Who's so rude she snores her
head off right next to the driver?

547
00:32:16,881 --> 00:32:21,161
I was up all night working on
the work instructions for the manager.

548
00:32:21,321 --> 00:32:23,521
Well, I stayed up
all night writing...

549
00:32:23,591 --> 00:32:26,191
a recruitment offer
for that same manager.

550
00:32:26,261 --> 00:32:28,261
Then I can just drive, can't I?

551
00:32:28,331 --> 00:32:31,871
Fine, let's do that.
We'll switch at the next rest stop.

552
00:32:33,301 --> 00:32:35,241
And to think you used to
cover my eyes...

553
00:32:35,301 --> 00:32:37,041
so the car lights wouldn't wake me.

554
00:32:37,711 --> 00:32:41,011
Hey, what's with you
bringing up the past all the time?

555
00:32:41,011 --> 00:32:42,081
Don't tell me...

556
00:32:42,081 --> 00:32:43,911
you still have feelings for me
or something?

557
00:32:45,311 --> 00:32:49,451
As if. I'm reminded every day how
lucky I was to break up with you.

558
00:32:56,791 --> 00:32:57,791
Hey, Woo!

559
00:32:58,191 --> 00:32:59,591
I mean...

560
00:32:59,861 --> 00:33:01,201
In-law.

561
00:33:01,831 --> 00:33:03,401
What? Where are you off to?

562
00:33:03,561 --> 00:33:07,441
Jason found a stylist position for me,
so I'm going to check it out.

563
00:33:08,001 --> 00:33:09,101
But why all the luggage?

564
00:33:09,471 --> 00:33:12,311
It's an overnight thing.
There's an information session...

565
00:33:12,311 --> 00:33:14,381
and then a hands-on workshop.

566
00:33:14,781 --> 00:33:15,781
Where is it?

567
00:33:16,111 --> 00:33:20,511
Wondam University Studio Village?
Anyway, I've got to go.

568
00:33:20,821 --> 00:33:21,821
In-law.

569
00:33:23,751 --> 00:33:24,791
Oh my.

570
00:33:27,591 --> 00:33:29,491
Wondam University Studio Village...

571
00:33:31,791 --> 00:33:33,891
How can you be getting this wrong?

572
00:33:34,431 --> 00:33:35,461
I'm sorry.

573
00:33:35,801 --> 00:33:38,601
Why is this confusing?
The answer is obviously two.

574
00:33:40,001 --> 00:33:42,601
I thought it was either
three or five.

575
00:33:43,471 --> 00:33:45,111
I told you,
you can never use "that,"

576
00:33:45,171 --> 00:33:46,871
after a non-restrictive comma.
Got it?

577
00:33:48,141 --> 00:33:49,411
Hey, are you in a bad mood?

578
00:33:50,141 --> 00:33:51,181
No, why?

579
00:33:51,781 --> 00:33:52,781
Just asking.

580
00:33:53,281 --> 00:33:54,681
You just seem a little angry.

581
00:33:55,721 --> 00:33:57,651
You shouldn't let your mood
affect your behavior.

582
00:34:00,421 --> 00:34:01,421
Sorry.

583
00:34:14,541 --> 00:34:15,771
I mean...

584
00:34:16,201 --> 00:34:19,311
We had to wait an hour
when we're this busy.

585
00:34:19,411 --> 00:34:21,811
Did we really need to come here
of all places?

586
00:34:22,211 --> 00:34:24,651
Yes. This place was
featured on Episode 130...

587
00:34:24,651 --> 00:34:26,011
of "Everyday Meals Across Korea."

588
00:34:26,011 --> 00:34:27,921
It's famous
for its dried pollock combo.

589
00:34:28,221 --> 00:34:30,081
It's a problem for me
when you indulge...

590
00:34:30,151 --> 00:34:32,021
your personal hobbies
on company time.

591
00:34:32,091 --> 00:34:34,661
Come on, just enjoy it.

592
00:34:34,961 --> 00:34:37,461
Eating delicious food in
the middle of a workday, you know?

593
00:34:37,631 --> 00:34:40,131
It's an investment in improving
our work efficiency.

594
00:34:40,961 --> 00:34:42,461
Why do I even bother?

595
00:34:49,241 --> 00:34:50,541
What is it now?

596
00:34:50,701 --> 00:34:53,241
That's not how you're supposed
to eat it.

597
00:34:53,771 --> 00:34:56,681
Here, on top of this thistle rice,

598
00:34:58,551 --> 00:34:59,881
the dried pollack,

599
00:35:00,181 --> 00:35:03,781
the bonnet bellflower root,
and pork belly.

600
00:35:04,591 --> 00:35:06,651
You have to eat it all
in one big bite.

601
00:35:07,721 --> 00:35:08,791
In one big bite.

602
00:35:11,331 --> 00:35:13,831
Let's just eat it however we want.

603
00:35:15,131 --> 00:35:17,671
The savory oil
from this pork belly...

604
00:35:17,931 --> 00:35:21,271
gently coats the clean umami
of the dried pollack...

605
00:35:21,301 --> 00:35:23,001
and just as the slightly
bitter aroma...

606
00:35:23,071 --> 00:35:25,071
when the bonnet bellflower root's
bitter aroma begins to rise...

607
00:35:25,311 --> 00:35:29,041
This.
The thistle rice's subtle flavor...

608
00:35:37,451 --> 00:35:39,021
Yes, Manager Oh.

609
00:35:40,251 --> 00:35:41,291
Right.

610
00:35:41,791 --> 00:35:44,761
Yes. Oh, then take your time
and come when you're done. Yes.

611
00:35:45,231 --> 00:35:46,261
Yes.

612
00:35:46,961 --> 00:35:50,301
How could you just
show up unannounced?

613
00:35:50,501 --> 00:35:54,301
Come on, if I'd called ahead,
you know we would've been rejected.

614
00:35:54,501 --> 00:35:57,871
Still, ambushing them like this
will just make them feel pressured.

615
00:35:57,941 --> 00:35:59,771
Look, when you're trying to
recruit a master,

616
00:35:59,841 --> 00:36:01,781
like this, you have to
show up unannounced...

617
00:36:01,841 --> 00:36:05,081
and show them how desperate we are.
That's the most effective method.

618
00:36:05,811 --> 00:36:09,321
Seriously, I wish I could make
those lips vanish.

619
00:36:09,721 --> 00:36:11,421
Gosh.

620
00:36:16,761 --> 00:36:17,891
How about here?

621
00:36:18,391 --> 00:36:20,461
My goodness.

622
00:36:21,331 --> 00:36:22,461
Right here, slightly here.

623
00:36:22,961 --> 00:36:26,231
- Oh, my goodness.
- Snacks in the break room.

624
00:36:26,301 --> 00:36:28,441
Hold on, I want to watch this
a little longer.

625
00:36:29,241 --> 00:36:33,441
With this much pain, it must have
been difficult for you to even walk.

626
00:36:33,841 --> 00:36:36,981
Yes. It's fine when I'm still,

627
00:36:37,311 --> 00:36:39,451
but it hurts when I move.

628
00:36:39,711 --> 00:36:41,981
This morning, when I got out of bed
and started walking,

629
00:36:42,681 --> 00:36:44,821
it hurt so much. Gosh.

630
00:36:46,621 --> 00:36:48,991
Sounds like plantar fasciitis.

631
00:36:50,491 --> 00:36:51,831
Father...

632
00:36:52,531 --> 00:36:54,431
What did you just say?

633
00:36:54,961 --> 00:36:58,031
You're right. What did I just say?

634
00:36:58,231 --> 00:37:01,471
It seems his memory is coming back.

635
00:37:12,781 --> 00:37:14,151
Why? Are you remembering something?

636
00:37:15,681 --> 00:37:17,351
I don't remember a thing.

637
00:37:17,791 --> 00:37:21,721
It'd be strange if you did.
I had the whole place remodeled.

638
00:37:23,321 --> 00:37:26,691
- Did you drink the Memory Tonic?
- I did.

639
00:37:27,091 --> 00:37:30,801
- Is that why? Memory's coming back.
- Oh, really?

640
00:37:31,501 --> 00:37:33,231
Then let's play a game
of Korean chess. It's been a while.

641
00:37:33,631 --> 00:37:36,301
- I play Korean chess?
- Do you ever.

642
00:37:37,201 --> 00:37:38,911
I've never beaten you.
Not even once.

643
00:37:44,381 --> 00:37:45,811
- Check.
- Wow.

644
00:37:45,881 --> 00:37:47,981
How about that? There's no way out
this time, is there?

645
00:37:51,751 --> 00:37:53,951
Check escaped and check.

646
00:37:55,891 --> 00:37:57,891
What's this?
When did this piece get here?

647
00:37:58,331 --> 00:37:59,631
Father, it looks like
you're going to lose again.

648
00:37:59,991 --> 00:38:02,561
You were faking it when you said
you lost your memory, weren't you?

649
00:38:02,931 --> 00:38:06,071
What, because you're still
losing to me after 30 years,

650
00:38:06,231 --> 00:38:07,231
you're scared?

651
00:38:07,571 --> 00:38:10,071
Why, you. Gosh...

652
00:38:11,471 --> 00:38:14,411
- Hey now.
- Come on, just take it.

653
00:38:20,151 --> 00:38:23,151
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

654
00:38:26,691 --> 00:38:29,561
You said you were just looking around.
What took you so long?

655
00:38:29,891 --> 00:38:31,161
Were you waiting?

656
00:38:32,461 --> 00:38:34,261
I was just playing a game
of Korean chess.

657
00:38:34,331 --> 00:38:35,731
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

658
00:38:35,801 --> 00:38:36,801
Good for you.

659
00:38:37,431 --> 00:38:38,501
Go on, get inside.

660
00:38:47,781 --> 00:38:49,411
(Onjeong Traditional Market)

661
00:38:58,451 --> 00:39:02,261
Woo Jae, what's a dish
the whole family would enjoy?

662
00:39:02,591 --> 00:39:04,431
Everyone would like something
like braised short ribs, right?

663
00:39:04,861 --> 00:39:09,161
Yes, I'm sure they would.
But don't make it. Understood?

664
00:39:09,901 --> 00:39:10,961
Why?

665
00:39:16,471 --> 00:39:18,371
Hello? Oh, hi, Min Seo.

666
00:39:18,641 --> 00:39:21,211
Woo Jae, have you heard from Eun Bin
by any chance?

667
00:39:21,681 --> 00:39:22,681
Eun Bin? Why?

668
00:39:23,041 --> 00:39:25,511
Oh, it's about Jason,
the guy I introduced to her.

669
00:39:25,851 --> 00:39:27,451
Apparently, he's a bad person.

670
00:39:27,681 --> 00:39:29,421
I guess I didn't really know him
when I introduced them.

671
00:39:29,751 --> 00:39:32,091
I'm worried because I can't
get in touch with Eun Bin.

672
00:39:32,391 --> 00:39:34,821
Okay, I got it.

673
00:39:35,961 --> 00:39:37,361
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

674
00:39:37,491 --> 00:39:40,661
Ma'am, something urgent came up,
so I have to leave now.

675
00:39:40,761 --> 00:39:42,301
What? Okay...

676
00:39:43,761 --> 00:39:45,631
Hey, Mom, I need to use the car.

677
00:39:52,441 --> 00:39:54,011
The phone is currently turned off...

678
00:39:54,011 --> 00:39:57,011
and will be forwarded to voicemail.

679
00:39:57,241 --> 00:39:59,081
This is driving me nuts.

680
00:39:59,711 --> 00:40:01,181
Where is she?

681
00:40:02,081 --> 00:40:03,351
Should I call the police?

682
00:40:13,361 --> 00:40:14,361
Eun Bin!

683
00:40:15,901 --> 00:40:16,901
Eun Bin!

684
00:40:18,101 --> 00:40:19,101
Yang Eun Bin!

685
00:40:22,671 --> 00:40:23,671
Eun Bin!

686
00:40:24,571 --> 00:40:25,571
Eun Bin!

687
00:40:27,641 --> 00:40:29,681
- Hey!
- Eun Bin!

688
00:40:33,051 --> 00:40:35,521
Hey. Yang Eun Bin. Stop right there!

689
00:40:36,351 --> 00:40:38,551
- Seriously.
- Hey. Yang Eun Bin!

690
00:40:38,621 --> 00:40:40,651
Stay away!

691
00:40:41,961 --> 00:40:45,831
- Hey. Where are you going?
- Stop following me.

692
00:40:46,991 --> 00:40:48,461
- Hey.
- That hurts.

693
00:40:48,531 --> 00:40:49,731
Come on, what's the problem?

694
00:40:49,731 --> 00:40:50,931
You have to tell me.

695
00:40:51,031 --> 00:40:53,101
Fine, let go. What are you doing?

696
00:40:53,171 --> 00:40:54,601
- What's wrong with you?
- Eun Bin.

697
00:40:56,201 --> 00:40:57,201
Are you okay?

698
00:41:00,111 --> 00:41:03,681
- Hey, who are you?
- Who are you?

699
00:41:04,111 --> 00:41:05,651
You're the part-timer
from the barbecue joint?

700
00:41:06,251 --> 00:41:08,251
That's Woo Jae.
He went to med school, you know.

701
00:41:08,321 --> 00:41:11,221
Med school, my ass. What gives
you the right to hit someone?

702
00:41:11,291 --> 00:41:12,791
What do you think you're doing?

703
00:41:13,421 --> 00:41:15,691
It's a pyramid scheme.

704
00:41:16,091 --> 00:41:17,791
- What?
- They took my phone...

705
00:41:17,791 --> 00:41:20,561
and wouldn't let me go home.
So I ran away.

706
00:41:24,331 --> 00:41:26,701
Hey, go get her phone
and her things right now.

707
00:41:27,301 --> 00:41:30,041
- Before I call the police.
- Before we call the police.

708
00:41:42,151 --> 00:41:43,151
Woo Jae...

709
00:41:45,521 --> 00:41:47,051
Gosh, why are you barefoot?

710
00:41:48,591 --> 00:41:52,491
I was in such a hurry I lost them.

711
00:41:57,261 --> 00:41:59,771
Oh, it's fine.
There's a convenience store.

712
00:42:00,001 --> 00:42:01,201
I can just buy some slippers.

713
00:42:01,571 --> 00:42:02,841
Want a piggyback,
or do you want to wear these?

714
00:42:05,111 --> 00:42:06,211
I'll wear them.

715
00:42:24,121 --> 00:42:26,461
Woo Jae, are you mad?

716
00:42:29,731 --> 00:42:30,831
Why would I be mad?

717
00:42:31,431 --> 00:42:32,601
I was just worried.

718
00:42:35,441 --> 00:42:38,071
Woo Jae, thank you.
No, I mean, in-law.

719
00:42:55,161 --> 00:42:57,421
- Hey!
- Oh, you scared me. What is it?

720
00:42:57,491 --> 00:42:59,191
I was just on my way
to the Police Substation.

721
00:42:59,361 --> 00:43:01,231
Well, I wanted to see you
even one minute sooner,

722
00:43:01,231 --> 00:43:02,331
so I came to you.

723
00:43:02,961 --> 00:43:05,671
- But we saw each other at lunch.
- I know, right?

724
00:43:06,071 --> 00:43:07,131
It's no use. The more I see you...

725
00:43:07,201 --> 00:43:08,571
the more I miss you.
It's becoming a problem.

726
00:43:08,671 --> 00:43:11,201
If it's going to be like this, maybe
we should just get married too?

727
00:43:11,411 --> 00:43:13,771
Do you want to get married soon,
Jin Ah?

728
00:43:14,371 --> 00:43:15,741
Not really.

729
00:43:16,211 --> 00:43:19,451
Seeing the manager get married
and look so happy...

730
00:43:19,551 --> 00:43:20,681
it makes me a little jealous.

731
00:43:20,981 --> 00:43:23,651
Then this weekend...

732
00:43:24,121 --> 00:43:25,391
would you like to come over
and meet my parents?

733
00:43:27,451 --> 00:43:30,291
Meet them? You're making me blush.

734
00:43:31,431 --> 00:43:33,031
Hey, where are you going?
Why? Where are you off to?

735
00:43:33,031 --> 00:43:35,731
Hey, let's go together.
You should be more careful.

736
00:43:36,131 --> 00:43:37,131
Thank you.

737
00:43:41,671 --> 00:43:42,671
Excuse me?

738
00:43:49,211 --> 00:43:50,211
Are you by any chance...

739
00:43:54,751 --> 00:43:56,181
- Oh, are you okay?
- Are you all right?

740
00:43:56,251 --> 00:43:58,021
- Yes, I'm fine.
- Oh, wait, be careful.

741
00:44:03,091 --> 00:44:05,261
Yes, this is Officer Jung
from the Onjeong Police Substation.

742
00:44:06,091 --> 00:44:07,761
I've spotted the wanted fugitive,
Jo Mi Hyang.

743
00:44:08,201 --> 00:44:10,561
Yes, requesting immediate backup
from all nearby units.

744
00:44:12,031 --> 00:44:14,471
Jo Mi Hyang is in Onjeong?

745
00:44:16,801 --> 00:44:19,971
Yes, I understand.
Yes, I'll do that.

746
00:44:21,511 --> 00:44:22,711
That woman is in Onjeong?

747
00:44:23,181 --> 00:44:26,981
Officer Jeong just spotted her
and gave chase...

748
00:44:26,981 --> 00:44:28,051
but it looks like he lost her.

749
00:44:28,621 --> 00:44:31,691
They're securing the surrounding
CCTV footage and tracking her now.

750
00:44:31,991 --> 00:44:35,061
Did she come here to get to Father?

751
00:44:35,521 --> 00:44:38,631
Probably.
Father, for the time being,

752
00:44:38,631 --> 00:44:40,531
it's probably best you refrain
from going out.

753
00:44:41,031 --> 00:44:43,361
I won't go out. I'll be careful.

754
00:44:44,161 --> 00:44:47,531
Yes, Father. For now,
just stay home with me.

755
00:44:48,501 --> 00:44:50,401
We need to double-check the locks.

756
00:44:51,571 --> 00:44:54,611
I'm sorry. For making everyone
go through this because of me.

757
00:45:02,021 --> 00:45:03,351
(Cabinetry Factory)

758
00:45:17,461 --> 00:45:19,631
Oh my, hello.

759
00:45:20,171 --> 00:45:21,471
Oh, hello.

760
00:45:21,941 --> 00:45:24,501
- You work here?
- Oh, yes.

761
00:45:24,771 --> 00:45:26,011
But what brings you here?

762
00:45:26,311 --> 00:45:29,681
Is Director Yang Hyun Bin in?

763
00:45:29,981 --> 00:45:32,311
Oh, Director Yang went on
a business trip...

764
00:45:32,311 --> 00:45:33,881
to Gangwon with CEO Gong.

765
00:45:34,311 --> 00:45:35,351
CEO Gong?

766
00:45:36,481 --> 00:45:37,521
CEO Gong?

767
00:45:38,081 --> 00:45:39,991
Oh, Gong Ju Ah.

768
00:45:41,221 --> 00:45:42,221
Wait, but...

769
00:45:42,791 --> 00:45:44,391
They went on a business trip
to Gangwon?

770
00:45:44,461 --> 00:45:45,461
Just the two of them?

771
00:45:46,491 --> 00:45:48,501
- Well...
- Oh my, hello.

772
00:45:50,201 --> 00:45:53,631
Oh, you're here too, Vice President.

773
00:45:56,541 --> 00:46:00,011
I heard about your father.
I'm sure this is difficult for you.

774
00:46:00,711 --> 00:46:01,941
Yes, I'm all right.

775
00:46:02,511 --> 00:46:04,381
Director Yang has been
a great support.

776
00:46:04,981 --> 00:46:07,111
Oh, really? Oh, that's good to hear.

777
00:46:07,581 --> 00:46:11,281
Well, you live nearby, you should
come over to my place sometime.

778
00:46:11,351 --> 00:46:12,921
I'll make you a nice,
home-cooked meal...

779
00:46:13,321 --> 00:46:16,821
Oh, I'm sorry. Sorry, just a moment.

780
00:46:19,961 --> 00:46:20,961
Yes, honey.

781
00:46:23,361 --> 00:46:24,361
What?

782
00:46:25,101 --> 00:46:26,101
Right now?

783
00:46:29,071 --> 00:46:30,101
Well...

784
00:46:34,671 --> 00:46:36,641
You ran into the Vice President
there too?

785
00:46:37,311 --> 00:46:38,311
Yes.

786
00:46:38,951 --> 00:46:42,181
Honey, if you keep this up,
Hyun Bin is going to flip out again.

787
00:46:42,781 --> 00:46:44,581
Oh, I just went
because I was really curious.

788
00:46:44,581 --> 00:46:46,551
I was just so curious.

789
00:46:46,891 --> 00:46:49,891
Stop that and pay
attention to me now. Me.

790
00:46:50,221 --> 00:46:52,931
What's there for me
to be concerned about?

791
00:46:53,231 --> 00:46:56,931
I'm going for a round of golf
with Councilor Hwang this weekend.

792
00:46:58,231 --> 00:46:59,231
Really?

793
00:46:59,571 --> 00:47:03,101
And during nomination season, too.
This is a really huge signal.

794
00:47:03,241 --> 00:47:04,241
Right?

795
00:47:04,301 --> 00:47:07,841
Oh, yes. Honey. I think we
can expect some good news.

796
00:47:08,411 --> 00:47:10,711
So, stop worrying about the kids...

797
00:47:11,141 --> 00:47:14,051
and have fun with me now, okay?

798
00:47:15,181 --> 00:47:17,421
Okay.
I'll pay more attention to you.

799
00:47:17,781 --> 00:47:19,691
Then, to prepare
for the nomination screening,

800
00:47:19,751 --> 00:47:21,661
we should get
your community activity records...

801
00:47:21,721 --> 00:47:22,721
and policy proposals.

802
00:47:22,791 --> 00:47:26,661
No, I don't mean
pay attention to my work.

803
00:47:27,061 --> 00:47:29,301
I mean let's focus on each other.

804
00:47:29,861 --> 00:47:32,901
So you won't have a moment
to feel lonely...

805
00:47:33,171 --> 00:47:35,141
I'll really try harder. Okay?

806
00:47:37,071 --> 00:47:38,411
Okay, honey.

807
00:47:39,441 --> 00:47:40,771
I'll try harder.

808
00:47:41,881 --> 00:47:43,641
Looks like I've been prescribed
some of your love.

809
00:47:44,681 --> 00:47:45,681
Whatever.

810
00:47:52,051 --> 00:47:56,661
Gosh, I knew this would happen.
What a wasted trip.

811
00:47:57,061 --> 00:48:00,191
It's better than giving up
without even trying.

812
00:48:00,361 --> 00:48:02,031
You call that an excuse?

813
00:48:02,761 --> 00:48:05,731
Well, then you shouldn't have failed
to convince Manager Oh.

814
00:48:06,631 --> 00:48:08,101
Are you blaming me for this?

815
00:48:09,841 --> 00:48:12,471
I'll look for another option,
so just wait.

816
00:48:12,671 --> 00:48:15,141
Wait for what?
For this exact situation,

817
00:48:15,241 --> 00:48:17,781
you should have had a Plan
B, C, and D ready to go.

818
00:48:17,981 --> 00:48:21,621
Having a backup plan
makes you less desperate...

819
00:48:21,981 --> 00:48:24,881
and I was worried it would make
it harder to win over Manager Oh.

820
00:48:24,951 --> 00:48:28,691
You've got an answer for everything.

821
00:48:29,061 --> 00:48:30,061
Don't worry.

822
00:48:30,891 --> 00:48:34,661
I'm the type who thrives in a crisis
and finds a better way.

823
00:48:34,891 --> 00:48:38,501
A talent like Manager Oh,
with both speed and quality,

824
00:48:38,571 --> 00:48:41,131
- are not easy to find, you know?
- Gosh, seriously.

825
00:48:41,471 --> 00:48:43,941
Oh, wait. What's wrong with the car?

826
00:48:44,201 --> 00:48:46,011
- What? Why?
- What?

827
00:48:55,451 --> 00:48:56,651
(Auto Repair Shop)

828
00:48:56,721 --> 00:48:57,921
How long will it take?

829
00:48:58,691 --> 00:49:01,491
It's not a big deal,
but we don't have the part.

830
00:49:01,921 --> 00:49:03,791
We won't be able to get it
until tomorrow morning.

831
00:49:04,091 --> 00:49:06,431
Gosh, we're in trouble.

832
00:49:07,961 --> 00:49:08,961
What should we do?

833
00:49:09,361 --> 00:49:10,461
What do you mean,
"what should we do?"

834
00:49:11,061 --> 00:49:13,871
We just have to find a place
to stay nearby.

835
00:49:14,371 --> 00:49:16,771
You should call a taxi
and head back.

836
00:49:17,301 --> 00:49:20,671
- I'll just wait until...
- No. That's even scarier.

837
00:49:20,711 --> 00:49:21,711
Excuse me...

838
00:49:22,411 --> 00:49:24,481
We actually run a bed and breakfast.

839
00:49:30,181 --> 00:49:31,821
Did you say you only have one room?

840
00:49:32,291 --> 00:49:33,291
Yes.

841
00:49:33,991 --> 00:49:34,991
Why?

842
00:49:35,161 --> 00:49:37,391
It's because we need to maintain...

843
00:49:37,461 --> 00:49:39,261
some distance from each other.

844
00:49:39,631 --> 00:49:42,961
I thought you two were a couple.

845
00:49:42,961 --> 00:49:44,331
- Oh, no way.
- No way!

846
00:49:44,331 --> 00:49:45,701
- No, no, we're not.
- No, we're not.

847
00:49:45,771 --> 00:49:46,771
Oh, what do we do?

848
00:49:48,801 --> 00:49:50,171
Then...

849
00:49:51,141 --> 00:49:52,271
Nothing we can do, then.

850
00:49:52,911 --> 00:49:55,311
I'll sleep here, so you go
sleep somewhere else, Director Yang.

851
00:49:55,511 --> 00:49:57,111
How is that fair?

852
00:49:57,541 --> 00:49:58,811
Let's play rock, paper, scissors.
Okay?

853
00:49:59,951 --> 00:50:02,651
Gosh, you're so childish.

854
00:50:03,121 --> 00:50:05,091
Oh, it's no use.

855
00:50:05,091 --> 00:50:07,521
There are no other places to stay
in this town.

856
00:50:20,501 --> 00:50:21,501
What's that for?

857
00:50:21,571 --> 00:50:25,311
I'm worried you'll lose control
and make a move on me.

858
00:50:25,471 --> 00:50:29,281
- In your dreams.
- Who says I'm the one dreaming?

859
00:50:29,541 --> 00:50:32,051
Even if the world ended
and I was left alone with you,

860
00:50:32,111 --> 00:50:33,111
I wouldn't have
the slightest interest...

861
00:50:33,181 --> 00:50:37,751
This is nice. So nice.
This is so comfy.

862
00:50:38,051 --> 00:50:40,251
Gosh. I can't stand
the sight of you.

863
00:50:41,091 --> 00:50:43,321
Can't believe this.

864
00:50:44,721 --> 00:50:46,691
- Gosh
- Oh my.

865
00:51:01,571 --> 00:51:02,581
I'm thirsty.

866
00:51:17,261 --> 00:51:18,461
What are you doing out here
all by yourself?

867
00:51:19,461 --> 00:51:20,461
Oh, hey...

868
00:51:20,891 --> 00:51:23,461
I just couldn't sleep.

869
00:51:24,501 --> 00:51:27,831
Liar. Now that you're actually
in the same room as me,

870
00:51:27,901 --> 00:51:30,901
you can't control your feelings,
so you're self-quarantining, right?

871
00:51:32,441 --> 00:51:35,581
Are you disappointed that
I'm keeping my composure?

872
00:51:36,641 --> 00:51:38,951
Couldn't you wait any longer,
so you came out to find me?

873
00:51:39,811 --> 00:51:41,551
I came out because I was thirsty.

874
00:51:45,691 --> 00:51:46,691
Here.

875
00:51:48,221 --> 00:51:51,191
Gosh, you could've opened it for me.

876
00:51:51,191 --> 00:51:52,831
What do you have hands for?

877
00:51:53,131 --> 00:51:54,261
Open it yourself.

878
00:51:54,691 --> 00:51:55,701
So petty.

879
00:52:07,141 --> 00:52:08,141
But...

880
00:52:08,941 --> 00:52:10,681
looking at the night sky here...

881
00:52:11,911 --> 00:52:13,111
reminds me of that time we went...

882
00:52:13,911 --> 00:52:15,551
to Gaetdari Garden.

883
00:52:18,421 --> 00:52:19,421
It sure does.

884
00:52:21,021 --> 00:52:22,161
And...

885
00:52:22,761 --> 00:52:25,631
the Gaetdari Samhap and makgeolli
we had there were so good.

886
00:52:26,631 --> 00:52:28,131
You had fun teasing me back then...

887
00:52:28,191 --> 00:52:30,131
pretending not to recognize me,
didn't you?

888
00:52:32,001 --> 00:52:33,001
I did.

889
00:52:40,111 --> 00:52:41,571
But, Director Yang,

890
00:52:42,641 --> 00:52:48,081
why are you trying so hard
to save the Fashion Division?

891
00:52:50,551 --> 00:52:51,551
You don't remember?

892
00:52:52,591 --> 00:52:53,591
Remember what?

893
00:52:54,791 --> 00:52:57,391
What you said to me when you quit.

894
00:53:01,631 --> 00:53:05,201
Could I ask you for one last favor?

895
00:53:06,101 --> 00:53:07,101
Anything.

896
00:53:07,671 --> 00:53:10,571
Please protect
Taehan's Fashion Division.

897
00:53:16,311 --> 00:53:17,881
We broke up...

898
00:53:19,251 --> 00:53:20,651
before I could keep all my promises.

899
00:53:21,951 --> 00:53:23,451
So I wanted to at least make sure...

900
00:53:24,051 --> 00:53:25,451
I granted your last request.

901
00:53:47,171 --> 00:53:49,411
- I should get going.
- You should.

902
00:54:15,301 --> 00:54:16,301
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

903
00:54:17,371 --> 00:54:18,941
My Dolphin,
you worked so hard today.

904
00:54:19,511 --> 00:54:22,441
Want to go for a walk?
Or grab some chicken and beer?

905
00:54:23,311 --> 00:54:24,611
I need to get home.

906
00:54:27,881 --> 00:54:28,881
Dolphin.

907
00:54:32,051 --> 00:54:33,851
Did Mom ask you to buy all this?

908
00:54:34,251 --> 00:54:36,121
No, I'm making it
for breakfast tomorrow.

909
00:54:36,191 --> 00:54:38,461
Braised short ribs
and cabbage soybean paste soup.

910
00:54:39,991 --> 00:54:41,561
- Dong Suk.
- Yes?

911
00:54:41,631 --> 00:54:43,161
You don't have to.

912
00:54:43,631 --> 00:54:47,001
- You don't have to go to trouble.
- What are you talking about?

913
00:54:47,271 --> 00:54:50,271
My goal is to wake up
before Mother tomorrow.

914
00:55:05,151 --> 00:55:06,151
What the...

915
00:55:09,221 --> 00:55:10,461
What are you looking at?

916
00:55:11,161 --> 00:55:12,431
This is my spot.

917
00:55:24,541 --> 00:55:27,271
You really are a wild sleeper,
I'll give you that.

918
00:55:27,641 --> 00:55:29,311
You're always falling asleep
next to me.

919
00:55:30,111 --> 00:55:31,181
That's not true.

920
00:55:31,541 --> 00:55:34,981
Come on.
You did it at Gaetdari Garden...

921
00:55:35,051 --> 00:55:36,751
and you didn't go home
when I was sick...

922
00:55:36,751 --> 00:55:37,881
because you fell asleep next to me.

923
00:55:37,951 --> 00:55:42,261
- Am I wrong? I'm right. I am.
- Gosh.

924
00:55:42,921 --> 00:55:43,991
Seriously.

925
00:55:55,871 --> 00:55:57,201
Dolphin.

926
00:56:02,181 --> 00:56:03,181
What?

927
00:56:07,251 --> 00:56:08,251
Dolphin?

928
00:56:12,521 --> 00:56:13,521
Dolphin.

929
00:56:16,361 --> 00:56:18,391
What are you doing up alone?
You should've woken me.

930
00:56:18,661 --> 00:56:20,491
Why are you up?
You should've slept more.

931
00:56:20,561 --> 00:56:22,501
I was just soaking the meat
from yesterday.

932
00:56:25,901 --> 00:56:27,731
- What can I do to help?
- What?

933
00:56:28,301 --> 00:56:32,241
In that case, can you chop onions
and carrots for the braised ribs?

934
00:56:35,211 --> 00:56:36,211
My gosh.

935
00:56:45,451 --> 00:56:48,021
- He's already passed away.
- My brother is dead?

936
00:56:48,091 --> 00:56:52,361
- We have to call the police.
- Bring him back!

937
00:57:01,031 --> 00:57:04,671
What's wrong, Father?

938
00:57:05,471 --> 00:57:07,871
It's nothing.
I just had a nightmare.

939
00:57:08,211 --> 00:57:10,441
Are you all right?

940
00:57:11,611 --> 00:57:13,451
I'm just going to the restroom.

941
00:57:13,811 --> 00:57:15,721
Father.

942
00:57:17,081 --> 00:57:19,591
It's all right.
I'm not going anywhere.

943
00:57:19,951 --> 00:57:22,051
Don't worry and go back to sleep.

944
00:57:25,531 --> 00:57:26,891
Father, I...

945
00:57:38,201 --> 00:57:39,511
Mother, Seong Mi.

946
00:57:39,811 --> 00:57:40,811
Yes, come in.

947
00:57:41,941 --> 00:57:44,881
- It's just...
- Why are you up so early?

948
00:57:45,381 --> 00:57:46,881
What is it?

949
00:57:47,081 --> 00:57:49,551
Mom, Seong Mi, please stop Dong Suk.

950
00:57:49,981 --> 00:57:51,581
- Why?
- What?

951
00:57:57,691 --> 00:57:59,291
Hey, Dong Suk.

952
00:57:59,931 --> 00:58:03,031
Oh, you're up already?
Mother, Seong Mi.

953
00:58:03,901 --> 00:58:04,931
Dong Suk.

954
00:58:05,531 --> 00:58:07,531
Are you making braised short ribs
this early in the morning?

955
00:58:08,571 --> 00:58:10,801
Yes. I'm not sure
if the seasoning is right.

956
00:58:11,101 --> 00:58:12,311
I made some side dishes too.

957
00:58:20,181 --> 00:58:23,751
Why, Mother?
Did I do something wrong?

958
00:58:24,621 --> 00:58:26,291
Dong Suk, do you want to move out?

959
00:58:26,791 --> 00:58:27,791
What?

960
00:58:28,121 --> 00:58:30,961
Why, Mother?
Am I making you uncomfortable?

961
00:58:31,321 --> 00:58:33,491
This does make us uncomfortable,
Dong Suk.

962
00:58:33,831 --> 00:58:36,361
Braised short ribs
this early in the morning?

963
00:58:36,601 --> 00:58:38,331
I kept telling her it's fine,

964
00:58:39,231 --> 00:58:40,401
but she wouldn't listen.

965
00:58:41,171 --> 00:58:44,241
We like to keep things simple
around here.

966
00:58:45,171 --> 00:58:46,171
Oh, okay.

967
00:58:46,811 --> 00:58:50,011
At my parents' house,
my sister-in-law did all the cooking.

968
00:58:50,211 --> 00:58:53,081
So now that I'm married,
I thought it was my duty.

969
00:58:53,651 --> 00:58:57,581
Besides, Seong Mi is sick
and Father isn't well.

970
00:58:58,151 --> 00:59:00,351
It's the thought that counts.

971
00:59:01,491 --> 00:59:04,421
Just for today.
Starting tomorrow, you can sleep in.

972
00:59:05,361 --> 00:59:09,861
- Seong Mi...
- Dong Suk, this is your home now.

973
00:59:10,261 --> 00:59:12,431
Don't feel you have to tiptoe around us.
Just be comfortable, okay?

974
00:59:13,901 --> 00:59:14,901
Okay.

975
00:59:15,471 --> 00:59:19,741
I asked you to move in so I could be
a mother to you in In Ok's place,

976
00:59:20,311 --> 00:59:24,111
but if you act like this,
I'll feel I'm letting In Ok down.

977
00:59:25,281 --> 00:59:27,211
Yes, I understand.

978
00:59:28,151 --> 00:59:29,581
Mom, Seong Mi.

979
00:59:30,921 --> 00:59:31,981
Thank you.

980
00:59:39,431 --> 00:59:41,261
Gosh, Father.

981
00:59:44,201 --> 00:59:45,671
What are you doing?

982
00:59:47,001 --> 00:59:49,701
I'm making sure
I never forget my name again.

983
00:59:51,101 --> 00:59:52,101
What?

984
00:59:55,011 --> 00:59:57,441
(Gong Gi Cheol. I Am Gong Gi Cheol)

985
00:59:59,481 --> 01:00:00,681
Father...

986
01:00:01,281 --> 01:00:02,751
The person who did this to me.

987
01:00:04,051 --> 01:00:05,581
I remember who it was.

988
01:00:06,091 --> 01:00:08,221
What? Really?

989
01:00:08,821 --> 01:00:10,921
Mi Hyang did this to me.

990
01:00:11,591 --> 01:00:13,231
She hit me in the head with a rock.

991
01:00:13,891 --> 01:00:16,101
In the head with a rock?

992
01:00:17,831 --> 01:00:20,831
And for 30 years,
she called me "brother."

993
01:00:22,271 --> 01:00:25,001
Father, does this mean
you remember everything?

994
01:00:25,501 --> 01:00:28,011
No. But...

995
01:00:28,871 --> 01:00:30,411
I'm sure of one thing.

996
01:00:31,181 --> 01:00:33,681
- Father...
- I'm not a murderer.

997
01:00:34,581 --> 01:00:36,051
I didn't kill anyone.

998
01:00:37,551 --> 01:00:38,921
Of course.

999
01:00:39,321 --> 01:00:42,121
Father, you'd never do
something like that.

1000
01:00:49,661 --> 01:00:51,401
Why did you come out?

1001
01:00:52,201 --> 01:00:53,401
Oh please.

1002
01:00:53,731 --> 01:00:56,841
Hey, why'd you come out?
Go on inside. Father, please go in.

1003
01:00:57,171 --> 01:01:00,311
Don't worry.
I'm not going anywhere ever again.

1004
01:01:01,511 --> 01:01:04,541
That's right, Father.
We have our session today.

1005
01:01:04,741 --> 01:01:05,811
Sounds good.

1006
01:01:06,751 --> 01:01:08,011
And make sure you lock the doors.

1007
01:01:08,411 --> 01:01:10,821
Okay, don't worry.

1008
01:01:11,121 --> 01:01:13,091
- Okay, go on inside, Father.
- Have a good day.

1009
01:01:13,091 --> 01:01:14,151
We'll see you later.

1010
01:01:14,321 --> 01:01:15,321
Go on in.

1011
01:01:16,921 --> 01:01:18,561
- Okay, go on inside.
- Have a good day.

1012
01:01:24,831 --> 01:01:26,271
- Go on, get inside.
- Okay.

1013
01:01:26,301 --> 01:01:27,631
- Okay, go on in.
- Go inside.

1014
01:01:27,931 --> 01:01:30,141
She has everything
she could ever want,

1015
01:01:31,641 --> 01:01:33,671
and she dares to steal
my only brother?

1016
01:02:22,291 --> 01:02:25,161
(Recipe For Love)

1017
01:02:25,221 --> 01:02:27,261
If the evidence points to an ambush
with intent to harm,

1018
01:02:27,591 --> 01:02:30,231
this could be considered
a case of attempted murder.

1019
01:02:30,431 --> 01:02:32,771
Everyone, be careful
for the time being.

1020
01:02:32,901 --> 01:02:35,841
Take away that Taehan name tag,
and I'm really nothing.

1021
01:02:36,271 --> 01:02:39,771
There's only one place left.
What if this one doesn't work out?

1022
01:02:39,841 --> 01:02:42,011
You do it yourself
since we're in a rush. I'm leaving.

1023
01:02:42,011 --> 01:02:43,841
What? Director Yang. Hey!

1024
01:02:44,041 --> 01:02:45,481
We'll face
some serious opposition...

1025
01:02:45,541 --> 01:02:46,951
from the merchants
at Onjeong Market.

1026
01:02:47,011 --> 01:02:49,421
After all, the market is
the focal point of our plan,

1027
01:02:49,481 --> 01:02:51,921
so we'll inevitably
have to tear it all down.

1028
01:02:51,981 --> 01:02:54,751
It looks like you've already
picked a spot for the landmark.

1029
01:02:56,261 --> 01:02:58,721
- Father, I think this is it.
- Yes.

1030
01:03:01,291 --> 01:03:02,931
Let's get Hyun Bin married.

1031
01:03:04,301 --> 01:03:05,331
Pardon?

1032
01:03:05,672 --> 01:03:07,672
Dramaday.me
